{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4366629845","title":"Lead Solution Consultant","company":"Sitecore","location":"Manchester","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"http://app.jobvite.com/CompanyJobs/Job.aspx?c=qTR9Vfwy&j=o5YgzfwC&__jvst=Job+Board&__jvsd=LinkedIn","description":"About Us:   \n\nOur mission is to elevate leading brands through unforgettable digital connections with their customers. Sitecore delivers a composable digital experience platform that empowers the world’s smartest and largest brands to build lifelong relationships with their customers. A highly decorated industry leader, Sitecore is the leading company bringing together content, commerce, and data into one connected platform that delivers millions of digital experiences every day. Thousands of blue-chip companies including American Express, Porsche, Starbucks, L’Oréal, and Volvo Cars rely on Sitecore to provide more engaging, personalized experiences for their customers. Learn more at Sitecore.com. \n\nSitecore’s foundation is our diverse group of passionate, smart, innovative, and collaborative individuals located across four continents and in over 25 countries. Having a wide range of perspectives, experiences, and skills is what makes us the company we are today. The Sitecore values are what drive and unite us across the globe.   \n\nAbout the Role: \n\nWe are looking for a Solution Engineer with strong presentation skills as well as a strong technical and digital background. As a Solution Engineer, your primary responsibility is to deliver technical and strategic support throughout the entire sales cycle for both the internal sales teams as well as for partners, prospects and existing clients. Some of the largest and most complex enterprise solutions in the region, which will require a broad technical skillset and excellent business acumen and insights, will challenge you.\n\nWhat You’ll Do: \n\n\nSupport the sales team with technical aspects of the Sitecore sales processes Enable and assist partners in the prospecting phase to deliver the best possible solution proposal Deliver bespoke demonstration scenarios of the Sitecore software solutions Develop and deliver Proofs of Concept to Sitecore prospect organizations Deliver excellent demonstrations of the Sitecore products Occasional public speaking on events in the region Solution prototyping, delivery, skinning, and presentation Miscellaneous technical tasks as need arises Spending a portion of your time learning and upskilling on the platform and new and associated technologies and features. Writing technical answers and proposals to RFP, RFQ, RFI from prospects\n\n\nWhat You Need to Succeed: \n\n\nExperience with combining technical elements with business needs and business requirements of the clients Experienced at demonstrating software using a value based approach Demonstrate the ability to resolve more complex technical issues and integration of multiple products to create solutions An appreciation and understanding of cross-channel digital marketing Technologies Manage multiple opportunities in a calm manner Ability to absorb and integrate large amounts of information in short timescales Demonstrate excellent communication and presentation skills Excellent team player, able to work closely with other technical sales and business development colleagues, while at the same time understand the value of self-drive, and the ability to control and prioritize own time independently Committed to continuous professional development\n\n\nAdditional Skills That Could Set You Apart: \n\n\nSolid experience and understanding of one or more Web Content Management systems, e-commerce, or digital asset management systemsSolid experience with frontend technologies like HTML, CSS, React, Angular, Vue etc.Understanding of the MarTech landscape and trends including SaaS and Headless content solutions.\n\n\n Why you should click ‘Apply’: \n\n\nSales and Customer Success are the key to our success! We are tapping into an exciting $30B market opportunity that is still very much in its infancy and feel It’s never been a better time to join Sitecore as we look to grow by 30% YoY. Growth for us means growth for you and your career. Great team and company culture! You can find out more about our company culture in the Sales and Customer Success team and our commitment to creating a diverse and inclusive workplace, on our YouTube Channel. Thanks to the work of every employee globally, Sitecore has been recognized for award-winning Culture by Comparably."}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4384503344","title":"Senior Product Manager","company":"Acronis","location":"Schaffhausen","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://acronis.wd502.myworkdayjobs.com/acronis_careers/job/United-Kingdom---Remote/Senior-Product-Manager_R-100631?source=LinkedIn","description":"Acronis is a world leader in cyber protection, delivering natively integrated solutions that monitor, control, and protect the data that businesses and lives depend on. Driven by our passion to protect every workload, we’ve built the industry’s only all-in-one cyber protection platform. We are looking for a Senior Product Manager to join our mission of protecting the digital world.\n\nIn this role you will leverage deep security expertise to collaborate with forward-thinking engineers and excited customers to ensure we have the most competitive and relevant cybersecurity solutions for service providers and enterprise customers. You will work with the executive team to establish a winning strategy, and partner with our outstanding sales, and marketing to ensure market adoption and rapid growth.\n\nWhat You'll Do\n\nDefine and own the product vision, strategy, and roadmap for EDR and XDR platforms and beyond, aligning with business goals and customer needs.Lead cross-functional teams through the full product lifecycle - from ideation and research to launch and iterative improvement.Translate complex security requirements and threat intelligence into clear, actionable product specifications and user stories.Collaborate with threat researchers and engineers to integrate cutting-edge detection logic, automation, and response capabilities.Champion a customer-first mindset, using feedback from enterprise clients, support teams, and field engineers to prioritize features and improvements.Work with sales and marketing to craft compelling messaging, demos, and go-to-market strategies for new capabilities.Monitor competitive landscape and industry trends (e.g., AI-driven security, zero trust, cloud-native defense) to keep our products ahead of the curve.Measure product success through KPIs including adoption, detection accuracy, mean time to respond, customer satisfaction, and retention.\n\nWhat You Bring (experience & Qualifications)\n\n5+ years of product management experience, with at least 3 years focused on cybersecurity, threat detection, or security operations.Deep understanding of EDR/XDR attack vectors, customer scenarios, and security workflows.Proven track record of launching and scaling security products in enterprise environments.Ability to dive deep in technology and to convey complex ideas simply and clearly in written and verbal formats, including public speaking, demos and content development.Working proficiency level of English, both written and verbal\n\nBonus Points\n\nSpecific knowledge of MSP business models and the automation of their processes in service delivery. Additional knowledge of providers and B2B IT services highly desirable.Please submit your resume and application in English.\n\nWho We Are\n\nA Swiss company founded in Singapore in 2003, Acronis offers over twenty years of innovation with 15 offices worldwide and more than 1800 employees in 50+ countries. Acronis Cyber Protect is available in 26 languages in 150 countries and is used by over 20,000 service providers to protect over 750,000 businesses.\n\nOur corporate culture centers on innovation, accountability, and impact. We encourage our people to think boldly, challenge conventional approaches, and take ownership of outcomes. As a member of our global “A-Team,” you’ll operate in a high-growth, fast-paced environment where resilience, adaptability, and a commitment to continuous improvement drive success.\n\nOUR INTERVIEW PRACTICES\n\nTo ensure a fair and genuine hiring process, candidates are expected to participate in interviews without the use of AI tools, automated prompts, or third-party assistance. Interviews are designed to assess individual skills, experience, and communication style and we value authentic, real-time interaction.\n\nUse of AI or external assistance during live interviews may result in disqualification. For roles where AI skills are being evaluated, permitted use of AI tools will be clearly communicated in advance. Candidates may be asked to disable virtual backgrounds or participate in in-person interviews. All employment offers are contingent upon successful completion of applicable criminal, education and identity background checks.\n\nAcronis is an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to age, ancestry, color, marital status, national origin, physical or mental disability, medical condition, protected veteran status, race, religion, sex (including pregnancy), sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, or any other characteristic protected by applicable laws, regulations and ordinances.\n\n"}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4390949405","title":"Channel Sales Executive","company":"Ansys","location":"Canonsburg","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://ae.linkedin.com/jobs/view/channel-sales-executive-at-ansys-4390949405?position=15&pageNum=0&refId=T%2B5J2moqeVAkW7Sq50xmaA%3D%3D&trackingId=I099DhVrXpMgcFXri3q%2FhA%3D%3D","description":"We Are:At Synopsys, we drive the innovations that shape the way we live and connect. Our technology is central to the Era of Pervasive Intelligence, from self-driving cars to learning machines. We lead in chip design, verification, and IP integration, empowering the creation of high-performance silicon chips and software content. Join us to transform the future through continuous technological innovation.\nYou Are:You are a dynamic and driven sales professional who thrives in collaborative environments and is passionate about building strong partnerships. With a proven track record in the software industry, you understand the nuances of both indirect and direct sales, excelling at developing and nurturing relationships with channel partners and customers alike. Your consultative approach allows you to identify and address customer needs, ensuring optimal solutions and satisfaction at every touchpoint.You bring a strategic mindset to your work, leveraging data and market insights to inform your sales strategies and drive sustainable growth. Your leadership capabilities shine as you coach and motivate partner representatives, empowering them to reach new heights in their performance. Adaptable and resourceful, you navigate complex situations with ease, mediating issues and facilitating effective resolutions to maintain momentum and trust.Your communication and negotiation skills are second to none, enabling you to engage confidently with senior executives and key stakeholders across diverse cultures. Committed to continuous learning, you stay abreast of industry trends and best practices, ensuring you bring the latest thinking to every engagement. Fluent in English and Polish, you possess cultural sensitivity and a global perspective that enhances your effectiveness in a multinational environment. Above all, you are passionate about technology and innovation, eager to contribute to Synopsys’ mission and make a lasting impact in the region.\nWhat You’ll Be Doing:Driving sales of ANSYS, part of Synopsys solutions within a specified region through channel partners, embodying ANSYS, part of Synopsys Channel principles.Owning and executing the sales plan for your territory, ensuring growth targets are consistently met.Providing hands-on leadership for sales opportunities and guiding channel partner reps with a “sell-with” approach.Building and nurturing relationships with senior-level customer executives to unlock new market opportunities.Coaching and motivating channel partner representatives to enhance their ANSYS, part of Synopsys selling skills and performance.Conducting joint customer visits and ensuring timely completion of sales, technical, and principal trainings and certifications.Delivering accurate and timely sales forecasts; regularly reviewing pipeline and forecast with channel partners.Managing partner capacity and capabilities to ensure optimal coverage and effectiveness.Serving as the central point of contact for all sales matters at the partner, ensuring efficient workflows.Implementing ANSYS, part of Synopsys Partner Program initiatives, including marketing programs, to drive regional success and future growth.Mediating channel partner requests/issues and assisting in tactical solution strategies for customer satisfaction.Collaborating with ANSYS, part of Synopsys regional sales leaders to analyse market trends and define go-to-market strategies.\nThe Impact You Will Have:Accelerating sales growth and market penetration for ANSYS, part of Synopsys solutions in DubaiEmpowering channel partners with the skills and resources needed to succeed in a highly competitive market.Shaping the future of simulation and PLM software adoption among small and medium-sized businesses.Enhancing customer satisfaction and loyalty through effective resolution of issues and proactive engagement.Driving best practices in channel sales, contributing to Synopsys’ reputation as an industry leader.Supporting the implementation and success of the ANSYS, part of Synopsys Partner Program, fostering long-term growth.Contributing to strategic decisions through market analysis and feedback, shaping regional business direction.Facilitating seamless collaboration between channel partners and internal Synopsys teams for efficient operations.\nWhat You’ll Need:Bachelor’s degree in a technical, engineering, business, or related field.6+ years of successful sales, key accounts, and indirect channel account management experience in the software industry, OR 8+ years of relevant experience.Demonstrated understanding of scientific or technical software products/services, including pricing and licensing practices.Proven consultative selling skills and experience with complex sales cycles.Exceptional contract negotiation abilities with key accounts.Strong analytical, planning, and organizational skills.Fluent in English; Arabic language skills are a plus.Excellent time management, communication, and presentation skills.Ability to travel up to 50% of the time.MBA or advanced degree, and experience in simulation/PLM software industry are preferred.\nWho You Are:A collaborative leader who inspires and motivates others.Strategic thinker with a proactive approach to problem-solving.Effective communicator, able to engage with stakeholders at all levels.Adaptable and resilient, thriving in fast-paced environments.Customer-centric, always striving to deliver exceptional value.Detail-oriented with strong organizational skills.Committed to continuous personal and professional growth.\nThe Team You’ll Be A Part Of:You’ll join a high-performing, collaborative sales team focused on driving growth through strategic partnerships and channel excellence. The team is passionate about delivering value to customers and partners, leveraging deep industry expertise and innovative sales strategies. You’ll work closely with regional leadership, technical sales, marketing, and operational teams to ensure seamless execution and continuous improvement in channel engagement.\nRewards and Benefits:We offer a comprehensive range of health, wellness, and financial benefits to cater to your needs. Our total rewards include both monetary and non-monetary offerings. Your recruiter will provide more details about the salary range and benefits during the hiring process.\nAt Synopsys, we want talented people of every background to feel valued and supported to do their best work. Synopsys considers all applicants for employment without regard to race, color, religion, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, military veteran status, or disability.\n#LI-Remote, #LI-Hybrid, #AnsysJob"}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4402866375","title":"Closer","company":"TXM Solutions","location":"Dubai, United Arab Emirates","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://ae.linkedin.com/jobs/view/closer-at-txm-solutions-4402866375?position=41&pageNum=0&refId=T%2B5J2moqeVAkW7Sq50xmaA%3D%3D&trackingId=glFpo8GcocA95vDheY5Xag%3D%3D","description":"We are looking for a Closer\nRole type: Full-time, remote\nReports to: Founder\nCompensation: Base + commission + performance bonuses (details on request)Business OverviewOur client is a seven figure creator management agency. We manage marketing operations with backend monetization systems, and coach other agency owners on scaling their operations.Role SummaryWe’re hiring a full-time closer to take qualified sales calls and convert inbound leads into signed clients. Until the calendar is consistently full, this person will also help manage and run the sales department — handling new leads, tightening the sales process, and supporting day-to-day ops in the sales function. As call volume ramps, the role transitions into pure closing.Key Responsibilities• Run qualified sales calls and close new clients• Manage inbound lead flow and follow-up cadence• Help oversee the sales department during ramp-up (process, pipeline, CRM hygiene)• Report weekly on pipeline, close rate, and revenue• Work directly with the founder to refine pitch, positioning, and objection handlingCandidate ProfileMust-haves:• Current or recent experience in a sales role (closing or setting) at an agency, coaching business, or high-ticket offer• Coachable and open to training; not looking for autopilot• Organised enough to run a sales process, not just take calls• Looking for a long-term seat at a growing agency soon to be No1Nice-to-haves:• Experience in a fast paced sales environment• Experience supporting or managing a small sales team"}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4406301292","title":"Country Manager","company":"Narwhal Labs","location":"Bristol","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://ae.linkedin.com/jobs/view/country-manager-at-narwhal-labs-4406301292?position=1&pageNum=0&refId=T%2B5J2moqeVAkW7Sq50xmaA%3D%3D&trackingId=Ze5VrP%2BP6flVS%2Bu8fPzmdw%3D%3D","description":"📍 UAE💼 Full-time💰 up to AED 500,000 DOE\nAbout DeepBlue OS:DeepBlue OS is the Agentic AI Operating System built in Bristol. We run autonomous voice, SMS, email and WhatsApp communications for enterprise customers — deterministic, auditable, and built for regulated industries. Our Glass Box Architecture is what enterprise buys; our pricing is what SMBs need.In 2026 we're rolling internationally. Tier 1 markets are Ireland, Australia, UAE, and Saudi Arabia. The Country Manager is the first and only DeepBlue hire in-market — a solo operator who owns the full commercial picture, supported by the Global GTM Lead in Bristol.\nThe role:This is a builder role, not a manager role. The Country Manager owns one market's P&L from day one: partner acquisition, agency network, revenue, and market intelligence. There is no in-country team — full team setup follows only after market traction is proven at the 6-month gate. The Country Manager reports directly to the Global GTM Lead.The entry model is Deel EOR on Day 1. At month 6, if commercial gates are met, Narwhal incorporates a local entity and opens a Regus office. The Country Manager transitions from solo operator to team lead at that point.\nThe Narwhal expansion playbookIdentify — pick the one anchor partner whose distribution gives you bulk account volume (telco, MSP, trades platform).Prove — land them, white-label DeepBlue OS under their brand, process real volume.Scale — layer 5–10 local agencies on top of the anchor, open direct sign-ups, build vertical case studies.Move — hand the steady-state to a scaled team, take the learnings to the next vertical or country.\nWhat you ownRevenue for your market — from day one, with uncapped accelerators on channel revenueAnchor partner acquisition — the one deal that makes the whole market viable. You identify, qualify, pitch, and close it soloLocal agency network — recruited, enabled, and supported. 5–10 agencies operating by month 12Market intelligence — regulation, competition, partner moves — fed back to the Global GTM Lead weekly via Close CRM and SlackIn-country presence — trade events, industry associations, press, private C-suite dinners. You are DeepBlue in UAE6-month gate readiness — you own all the conditions that determine whether Narwhal commits to a permanent entity and office\nWho we're looking for\nEssential8–12 years B2B channel or enterprise sales in your target marketDeep network at Director level or above inside one of: the dominant telco, a major trades/services platform, or a leading MSPProven track record closing 6- and 7-figure partnerships — not account managementSelf-directed solo operator — comfortable with a remote HQ and no in-country support teamCommercially sharp: unit economics, pricing models, building a business case for a technical product\nAdvantageousExperience in AI, SaaS, communications technology, or platform/marketplace businessesExperience with white-label or channel distribution modelsTrack record building a market from scratch, not inheriting an established territory\nMarket-specific requirementsUAE — Business Arabic a strong advantage. Existing GCC network essential.\nWhat you getUncapped commission on partner and channel revenue, with accelerators on volume milestonesFull DeepBlue OS product training and Bristol onboarding in week oneQuarterly travel to Bristol HQ for SLT leadership offsites — flights and accommodation coveredClose CRM access, Cognism B2B data, and the full Bristol commercial infrastructure from day oneDirect line to the Global GTM Lead and CEO — no middle management\nWe don't run long recruitment processes. If you're right for this role, you'll speak to the Global GTM Lead within five working days. No recruiters - thank you."}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4402454959","title":"Head of Engineering","company":"Stealth B2B SaaS Company","location":"Dubai, United Arab Emirates","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://ae.linkedin.com/jobs/view/head-of-engineering-4402454959?position=9&pageNum=0&refId=T%2B5J2moqeVAkW7Sq50xmaA%3D%3D&trackingId=KMl6g%2B7LHTnGpDbHcP37Sw%3D%3D&trk=public_jobs_jserp-result_search-card","description":"Who are we\nAt Balio Software we acquire and scale niche B2B software companies worldwide, bridging the gap between traditional software stability and AI innovation. Our team consists of successful SaaS founders and investors who have accelerated companies into high-performing businesses. Today, we are driving systemic change across our portfolio by deploying an AI-first mindset. By integrating advanced AI solutions into the companies we purchase, we elevate market value and sharpen value propositions, enabling businesses to excel as agile, efficient, and modern organisations. We are operators at our core, powered by the future of intelligence.\nAbout the roleBalio is hiring a Head of Portfolio Engineering to set the technical direction for our portfolio of acquired software businesses and build the engineering function that will scale with us. This is a hands-on leadership role that sits at group level; working across every product and team in our portfolio, you'll raise the quality bar, consolidate infrastructure, and give our engineering teams the tools and standards to build AI-native by default. This is a fully remote role and you will work with teams across multiple time zones (AEST to PST).\nWhat you'll ownEngineering leadership across all portfolio companies, setting the technical direction, quality bar, and operating cadence.Hiring, developing, and holding accountable engineering leads at each portfolio company; building a bench of talent across the group.Driving an AI-first engineering approach, identifying where AI tooling, automation, and agents can accelerate product delivery and reduce manual overhead.Partnering with portfolio company GMs to translate business goals into technical roadmaps.Serving as the primary escalation point for engineering risk, architecture decisions, and major technical investments across the portfolio.Running a lightweight shared services function where applicable - identifying where tooling, infrastructure, or practices can be standardised across companies.Reporting directly to the Head of Portfolio you will serve as the technical lead within the Balio leadership team.\nWho you areA senior engineering leader - you've run engineering teams of 15+ people and know what good looks like across the full SDLC. Strong preference for experience managing across multiple teams.Broadly technically credible - across SDLC, architecture, infrastructure, and delivery, with strong mentorship and decision-support capability.Operationally sharp - comfortable managing across multiple products/companies simultaneously, with strong prioritisation instincts.An AI native - you use AI tools daily, you think about how to embed them in engineering workflows, and you hold a genuine conviction that AI changes how software gets built. The focus is practical productivity gains, not buzzword-led initiatives.A strong communicator - able to translate technical complexity for commercial stakeholders and vice versa.Comfortable with ambiguity - this role is being built; the right person will shape it.\nBackground we'd expect10+ years in software engineering, with 4+ years in an engineering leadership role (VP Eng, Head of Engineering, or equivalent).Experience in a multi-product or portfolio environment preferred (PE-backed, holding company, or venture studio).Track record of improving engineering velocity and quality in acquired or turnaround businesses.Experience shipping measurable quality or productivity gains using AI assisted workflows"}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4405553488","title":"HNW Investment Advisor (Golden Visa) – Gulf Region","company":"PassBeyond","location":"Athens","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://ae.linkedin.com/jobs/view/hnw-investment-advisor-golden-visa-%E2%80%93-gulf-region-at-passbeyond-4405553488?position=30&pageNum=0&refId=T%2B5J2moqeVAkW7Sq50xmaA%3D%3D&trackingId=nSTDW%2F1zw0XtUD6%2FwIazkw%3D%3D","description":"📍 Remote | Report to Athens HQ 💼 Independent Contractor 💰 Uncapped commission — top performers earn €100,000–€200,000+\nWho We Are\nWe believe ambitious people should not be prisoners of their passport.PassBeyond helps high-net-worth individuals secure European residency and citizenship through Greek property investment. Our clients invest €250,000–€800,000+ and receive residency or citizenship for themselves and their families — gaining Schengen access, euro-denominated assets, and long-term optionality.\nFounded by Andreas Afeldt, based full-time in Athens, who has spent over a decade working with high-net-worth clients across international markets. PassBeyond sits between global institutional scale and personal, founder-led trust — with deep local knowledge in Greece and cultural fluency across every market we serve.\nThe Role: Bring Your Network. We Bring Everything Else.\nThis is not a traditional sales role, and we are not building a call centre. We are looking exclusively for individuals who have already spent years — sometimes decades — building a personal network of high-net-worth entrepreneurs, business owners, investors, and senior professionals.\nYour network is the asset. Our job is to make it more valuable.\nIf you already move in the right circles, we give you a credible, high-value opportunity to introduce to the people who already trust you — backed by a full operational engine in Athens that handles legal, transactional, and immigration work for you.\nYou will:• Introduce PassBeyond to high-net-worth individuals already in your personal network • Activate dormant relationships with a substantive reason to reconnect • Help clients understand the real numbers, real timelines, and real risks — so they can make an informed decision • Walk alongside clients from first conversation through to permit in hand • Build trust through genuine conversation — not scripts or pressure tactics • Work remotely with full support from our Athens headquarters\nWe are not looking for cold-callers, lead-chasers, or people hoping to build a network from scratch on the job. We are looking for trusted connectors who already have one.\nWho Our Clients Are\n• Entrepreneurs, business owners, and investors with €250,000–€800,000+ to invest • Self-made successes who built wealth through talent and persistence • Often from environments where institutions have failed them — they are sceptical for good reason • Looking for optionality: security, Schengen access, European education, and peace of mind for their families • They value relationships over transactions and will not be rushed or pressured\nOur clients need someone who already understands their world, respects their scepticism, and guides with patience and honesty.\nWhat We're Looking For\nEssential:• An established personal network of high-net-worth individuals you can credibly introduce to a serious opportunity — this is non-negotiable • Cultural fluency — you genuinely belong to the communities you would serve, not just market to them • Fluent English (written and verbal) • Comfortable with commission-only compensation • Integrity — you would rather lose a deal than mislead someone in your network\nHighly Desirable:• Experience in real estate, immigration, wealth management, or financial servicesBackgrounds that often do well:• Business owners and entrepreneurs with peer networks of fellow founders • Private bankers and wealth managers with a client book they can speak to independently • Lawyers and accountants serving affluent clients • Real estate professionals active in investment or luxury markets • Community leaders and well-connected professionals with genuine standing in diaspora or HNW communities\nWhat You Get• Access to training and information about our programmes — no cost to you • Conversation guides designed for high-stakes, trust-based advisory — not generic sales scripts • CRM system for pipeline management • Branded marketing materials ready to share with your contacts • Direct support from our Athens headquarters — legal coordination, transaction management, and immigration filing handled for you • As we grow together, you will receive warm leads from our marketing campaigns alongside your own network"}
