ion and Product Segment.Engaging with ‘C’ level and key customer personas to promote the Digital Subsea & Surface Pressure Systems portfolio.Being a Trusted Advisor and Customer Champion, establishing partnership relationships with key clients.Introducing technical sales representatives, solution architects, and sales support teams for deep technical dives and understanding of the solutions.Leading efforts to establish and expand market share, own pipeline planning, creation, and maintenance.Collaborate with product development, engineering, marketing, and sales teams to align digital offerings with market demands and communicate value propositions effectively.Working with leaders across the organization to develop growth strategies across product offerings with complex and enterprise customers.\n\n\nTo be successful in this role:\n\n\nHold a Bachelor’s degree in Engineering or a related discipline; experience in enterprise software or digital solution sales within offshore, subsea, or upstream environments is highly valued.Bring strong domain expertise in Subsea & Surface Pressure Systems, with practical exposure to:\nSubsea production systems including Christmas Trees, manifolds, jumpers, umbilicals, and tie‑insSubsea and surface pressure control equipment and their integration with drilling, production, and facilities. \nDemonstrate a solid understanding of the subsea project and asset lifecycle, from design to installation and operations, including interpretation of EPC deliverables (e.g., P&IDs, interface drawings, installation procedures)Possess working knowledge of subsea flow assurance, hydraulics, and system integrity, and how these challenges impact reliability, availability, and production uptime.Show clear understanding of subsea control systems and integration, including interfaces between subsea equipment and topside control / SCADA systems.Be comfortable positioning digital and software-enabled solutions in a subsea context, such as Asset performance 