{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://fr.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=2012ab0846a828fe","title":"Cybersecurity Business Development Executive","company":"Dartificial","location":"{\"city\":\"Télétravail\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"France\",\"countryCode\":\"FR\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Télétravail\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Télétravail\",\"latitude\":25,\"longitude\":-40,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":\"Télétravail\"}","remote":true,"salary":"{\"salaryCurrency\":\"EUR\",\"salarySource\":\"EXTRACTION\",\"salaryText\":\"500 € par mois\",\"salaryType\":\"monthly\"}","posted_at":"8 days ago","url":"https://fr.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=2012ab0846a828fe","description":"Job Description – Cybersecurity Business Development Executive\n\nCompany: Dartificial – AI & Cybersecurity\nLocation: Remote (Europe)\nEmployment Type: Freelancer / Part-Time / Remote\nLanguage: English\nCompensation: 500 Eur per month + 5% commission per closed deal\n\n*About Dartificial*\n\nDartificial is a fast-growing AI and Cybersecurity company specializing in AI-powered Security Operations Center (SOC) solutions, Managed Detection & Response (MDR), and compliance-driven cyber defense services.\n\nWe help SMEs and mid-market companies in regulated industries such as BFSI, FinTech, HealthTech, and SaaS strengthen their cybersecurity posture through AI-driven threat detection, Blue Team automation, compliance readiness, and incident response solutions.\n\nAs part of our European expansion, we are looking for a Cybersecurity Business Development Executive to drive new client acquisition and expand our presence across the region.\n\n*Role Overview*\n\nThe Cybersecurity Business Development Executive will be responsible for generating leads, managing outbound campaigns, building client relationships, and closing cybersecurity service deals.\n\nThis role focuses exclusively on promoting SOC, MDR, cybersecurity compliance, and AI-based defense solutions to SMEs and mid-sized enterprises.\n\nYou will work closely with the founder and technical cybersecurity team for product demonstrations and solution discussions.\n\n*Key Responsibilities*\n\n* Identify and target SMEs and mid-market companies across Europe requiring cybersecurity services\n* Generate qualified leads through LinkedIn, email campaigns, events, and networking\n* Build and manage a strong sales pipeline using HubSpot CRM\n* Conduct discovery calls with CTOs, CIOs, CISOs, Heads of IT Security, and Compliance Leaders\n* Understand customer cybersecurity challenges related to:\n* SOC operations\n* incident response\n* threat monitoring\n* compliance requirements\n* cyber risk management\n* Pitch cybersecurity solutions including:\n* SOC / MDR services\n* AI-powered Blue Team defense\n* threat detection & response\n* DORA / NIS2 compliance solutions\n* Coordinate technical demos with internal cybersecurity specialists\n* Negotiate proposals, contracts, and close pilot or subscription deals\n* Submit weekly reports on KPIs, pipeline status, and deal progress\n\nRequired Skills & Experience\n\n* Professional fluency in English\n* 1–3 years of B2B sales experience, preferably in:\n* Cybersecurity\n* IT Services\n* SaaS\n* Managed Security Services\n* Experience in cold outreach and lead generation campaigns\n* Strong communication skills with both technical and C-level stakeholders\n* Self-driven, entrepreneurial, and target-oriented mindset\n* Familiarity with cybersecurity concepts such as:\n* SOC\n* MDR\n* SIEM\n* Blue Team operations\n* DORA / NIS2 compliance\n* is a strong advantage\n\nKPIs / Performance Metrics\n\n* 50–100 outreach messages per day\n* 3–6 meetings booked per week\n* 2–4 qualified cybersecurity opportunities per month\n* 1 closed deal every 1–2 months\n\nBenefits:\n\n* Fully remote work\n* Flexible schedule\n* Opportunity to work in cutting-edge AI-driven cybersecurity solutions\n* Long-term growth and partnership opportunities\n\nType d'emploi : Intérim\nDurée du contrat : 6 m