{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4404284948","title":"Senior Business Analyst","company":"HOIST","location":"Toronto","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://fr.linkedin.com/jobs/view/senior-business-analyst-at-hoist-4404284948?position=27&pageNum=0&refId=XpAiGCPEM7yX1Qav3JJGmw%3D%3D&trackingId=cQG0cD1DYGg4RCo95c%2Bsxw%3D%3D","description":"HOIST is expanding its presence in France, and we’re looking for a Senior Business Analyst (Finance) to play a pivotal role in that growth. This is a remote position based in France, working with clients and colleagues in France and across our global business.\nAt a glanceLocation / working model: France (remote), with travel to client sites as requiredLanguages: Fluent French + professional English. Applications welcome in English or French; interviews predominantly in English.Focus: Senior Finance BA on ERP/digital transformation (ideally IFS), owning workstreams and mentoring/coaching\nWho we areWe are an IFS integrator, offering comprehensive ERP implementation projects to unparalleled support services. As a business strategic partner, we collaborate with clients across focused industries, transcending boundaries to deliver transformative service. With a global team of 200+ members, our strength is in our shared expertise. Our community comprises former IFS customers who’ve encountered challenges firsthand and dedicated IFS experts who bring specialised knowledge to the table. Together, we reshape businesses through exceptional service.\nRole summaryFrance is a strategic growth market for HOIST. As Senior Business Analyst (Finance), you’ll lead discovery and requirements on ERP/digital transformation engagements, partnering with Finance stakeholders and HOIST delivery teams to shape workable solutions, manage scope, and support adoption.\nKey ResponsibilitiesLead workshops to elicit, analyse and validate Finance requirements; produce clear documentation (process maps, specs/user stories, acceptance criteria) with traceability.Map current/future processes, assess impacts (incl. controls), perform gap analysis and recommend pragmatic improvements.Partner with architects and delivery teams to translate needs into workable designs; support decisions and manage trade-offs.Own Finance workstreams end-to-end (scope, dependencies, risks/issues) and support data/integration discussions where Finance is impacted.Support testing/UAT and adoption (training, comms); mentor junior colleagues and contribute to internal best practice as we grow in France.\nMust-have requirements5+ years as a Business Analyst and/or ERP Functional Consultant with strong Finance expertise.ERP implementation/transformation experience across the lifecycle (requirements through to testing and adoption).Strong workshop facilitation and stakeholder management; confident with senior client contacts.Fluent French and professional English (written/spoken).Adaptable and hands-on — willing to build ways of working as the France region scales.Based in France with right to work; willing to travel to client sites as required.\nNice to haveExperience delivering within IFS Cloud / IFS ERP (Finance); IFS certification is a plus.Experience with other major ERP platforms (SAP, Oracle, Microsoft Dynamics) within Finance.Exposure to system integration, data migration, and reporting/analytics (including defining KPIs and Finance reporting requirements).Experience in one or more of the following industries: Manufacturing; Energy & Utilities; Service Sector; Construction & Engineering; Shipping & Harbour Services; Aviation & Defense.Experience coaching/mentoring colleagues and contributing to internal ways of working and reusable assets.\nWhy HOIST?If you’re driven by the desire to make a tangible impact, HOIST is your destination. Join a client-driven team delivering transformative business excellence, grounded in our Core Values: Customer Focus, Excellence through Expertise, Care for our People and Innovation. You’ll work in a collaborative environment with flexibility, autonomy, and the backing of a global community of experts.\nHow to applyPlease apply via the job posting, or contact the hiring team for an initial conversation. We welcome applications in English or French; please note the interview process will be predominantly conducted in English.\nWe will not be accepting applications from candidates based outside of France. We are not accepting engagement through recruitment agencies.\n\nHOIST accélère son développement en France et recrute un(e) Senior Business Analyst – Finance pour jouer un rôle clé dans cette dynamique. Ce poste est en télétravail, basé en France, avec des interactions régulières auprès de clients et de collègues en France et au sein de notre organisation internationale.\nEn brefLocalisation / mode de travail : France (télétravail), avec des déplacements chez les clients selon les besoinsLangues : Français courant + anglais professionnel. Candidatures acceptées en français ou en anglais ; entretiens majoritairement en anglais.Focus : Rôle senior Finance sur des projets ERP / transformation digitale (idéalement IFS), leader du champ de travail et du mentorat / coaching\nQui sommes-nous ?HOIST est un intégrateur IFS : nous accompagnons nos clients sur des projets d’implémentation ERP de bout en bout, ainsi que sur des services de support reconnus. Partenaire stratégique, nous intervenons dans des secteurs ciblés et aidons les organisations à réussir leur transformation, au-delà des frontières. Notre équipe internationale compte plus de 200 collaborateurs. Notre force : une expertise issue à la fois d’anciens clients IFS (qui connaissent les enjeux « terrain ») et d’experts IFS dédiés. Ensemble, nous mettons l’excellence du service au cœur de chaque mission.\nRésumé du posteLa France est un marché stratégique pour la croissance de HOIST. En tant que Senior Business Analyst – Finance, vous prendrez en charge le cadrage et la formalisation des besoins sur des projets ERP / transformation digitale. En lien étroit avec les équipes Finance côté client et les équipes HOIST, vous contribuerez à concevoir des solutions concrètes, à sécuriser le périmètre, et à faciliter l’adhésion au changement.\nResponsabilités principalesAnimer des ateliers pour recueillir, analyser et valider les besoins Finance ; produire une documentation structurée (cartographies de processus, spécifications / user stories, critères d’acceptation) tout en assurant la traçabilité.Cartographier les processus existants et cibles, évaluer les impacts (y compris contrôle interne), réaliser les analyses d’écarts et proposer des améliorations pragmatiques.Travailler main dans la main avec les architectes et les équipes projet pour transformer les besoins en solutions réalistes ; faciliter les arbitrages et les décisions.Piloter le champ de travail de Finance de bout en bout (périmètre, dépendances, risques/sujets) et contribuer aux échanges data / intégration dès lors que la Finance est impactée.Accompagner les phases de tests/UAT et l’adoption (formation, communication) ; soutenir la montée en compétences de profils juniors et contribuer au développement de nos bonnes pratiques en France.Exigences indispensables5+ ans d’expérience en tant que Business Analyst et/ou consultant(e) fonctionnel(le) ERP, avec une expertise Finance solide.Expérience sur des projets ERP / transformation sur l’ensemble du cycle (recueil des besoins, conception, tests, mise en production et adoption).Excellente capacité à animer des ateliers et à gérer les parties prenantes ; aisance avec des interlocuteurs de niveau Direction.Français courant et anglais professionnel (écrit/oral).Autonomie, adaptabilité et sens du concret : envie de structurer et d’améliorer nos modes de fonctionnement au fil de la croissance en France.Basé(e) en France avec le droit d’y travailler ; disponible pour des déplacements chez les clients selon les besoins.AtoutsExpérience sur des projets avec IFS Cloud / IFS ERP (Finance) ; certification IFS appréciée.Expérience sur d’autres solutions ERP majeures (SAP, Oracle, Microsoft Dynamics) dans un contexte Finance.Connaissance des sujets d’intégration, de migration de données et de reporting / analyse (dont définition de KPI et des besoins des rapports Finance).Expérience dans un ou plusieurs des secteurs suivants : Industrie manufacturière ; Énergie & services publics ; Services ; Construction & ingénierie ; Transport maritime & services portuaires ; Aéronautique & défense.Expérience de mentorat / coaching et contribution à des méthodes, standards et livrables réutilisables.\nPourquoi HOIST ?Vous avez envie d’avoir un impact concret chez vos clients, tout en évoluant dans un environnement bienveillant et exigeant ? Chez HOIST, vous rejoignez une équipe orientée client, qui accompagne des transformations ambitieuses, guidée par nos valeurs : Customer Focus, Excellence through Expertise, Care for our People et Innovation. Vous bénéficierez de flexibilité, d’autonomie, d’un collectif solide et du soutien d’une communauté internationale d’experts.\nComment postulerPostulez directement via l’annonce, ou contactez l’équipe recrutement pour un premier échange. Les candidatures sont acceptées en français ou en anglais ; à noter que le processus d’entretien se déroulera majoritairement en anglais.\nNous ne pourrons pas étudier les candidatures de personnes basées hors de France. Nous ne travaillons pas avec des agences de recrutement pour ce poste."}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4404458542","title":"Senior Strategy Consultant","company":"Planview","location":"Austin","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://fr.linkedin.com/jobs/view/senior-strategy-consultant-at-planview-4404458542?position=14&pageNum=0&refId=XpAiGCPEM7yX1Qav3JJGmw%3D%3D&trackingId=5F4PmqBg4W2T1foed9OuCQ%3D%3D","description":"Planview has one mission: to build the future of connected work, from ideas to impact.\nAs the global leader in work and resource management, Planview helps organizations accelerate the achievement of what matters most, supporting our customers from need to speed, from passion to progress, and from overhead to optimization. We provide the industry’s most comprehensive solutions designed for strategic planning, portfolio and resource management, Lean and Agile delivery, product portfolio management, capability, and technology management (enterprise architecture), innovation management, and collaborative work and project management. Our connected platform of solutions underpins the business and digital transformations of more than 4,500 customers globally, including 59 of the Fortune 100.\nAt Planview, our people connections drive our innovation and success. Our global team of 1400+ work remotely and across our offices including Austin, Vancouver, Hod Hasharon, Bangalore, Sydney, and Stockholm. We’re proud of our world-class, connected culture built on our shared values, that supports our teams to be successful from anywhere.\nLearn more about our portfolio at planview.com, and connect with us on LinkedIn, Instagram, and X.\nThe Opportunity\nWe are seeking a high-potential Senior Strategy Consultant to support executive transformation engagements across Europe.Working within Planview’s Global Enterprise Transformation team, you will help shape executive discussions with leading European enterprises through workshops, short engagements, strategic research, business case development, and transformation storytelling.This is a customer-facing advisory role, operating across both prospective and existing Planview customers.You will gain exposure to senior executives across major European organizations and collaborate with experienced strategists, sales leaders, transformation specialists and product teams to deliver high-impact executive engagements.Executive engagement at Planview is authentically focused on the clients’ transformation journey, but in service to sales of our analyst lauded and industry leading SaaS platform. This position offers exposure to diverse industries across Europe, including FTSE and DAX 100 clients, and collaborating with a team of experienced professionals.\nSpecial Project (First 3-6 months):You will lead the tailoring of our Transformation & Executive Engagement motion for the Central and Southern European region – adapting messaging, executive workshop design, and value narratives to regional market dynamics. Over time, you will increasingly own and scale this motion.\nWhat You'll Do\nExecutive & Transformation EngagementSupport the design and delivery of high-impact executive workshops for prospective and existing clientsConduct research and stakeholder analysis to understand client transformation challengesHelp facilitate transformation strategy engagements (~2–6 weeks)\nStrategy & Business Case DevelopmentDevelop executive-ready presentations and transformation roadmapsBuild CFO-quality business cases and value narrativesTranslate complex operational and strategic challenges into clear insights and recommendations\nSales & Growth SupportPartner with sales, solution, marketing, implementation and customer success teams to support strategic deal pursuitsContribute transformation narratives that align client priorities with Planview capabilitiesSupport account growth by identifying value expansion opportunities\nRegional Motion Development (Central & Southern Europe)Adapt transformation messaging and workshop formats for regional executive audiencesDevelop regionally relevant points of view and case examplesBuild reusable assets and playbooks to scale the motion\nThought Leadership & Insight DevelopmentContribute to transformation points of view combining industry trends, best practices, and Planview capabilitiesSupport development of executive-ready insights and workshop content\nWhat You'll Bring\nExperience4-6 years’ experience in management consulting, transformation delivery, or strategic advisoryExperience at a top-tier consulting firm or transformation practice strongly preferredExposure to operating model, digital transformation, portfolio management, or enterprise strategy work SkillsStrong executive storytelling capability, with excellent PowerPoint structuring and visualization skillsAdvanced Excel capability and experience building structured business casesAbility to synthesize complex qualitative and quantitative inputs into clear executive insightsStrong structured problem-solving capabilityEffective workshop facilitation, whiteboarding, and real-time synthesis skills (virtual and in-person)Experience leveraging AI tools to enhance consulting outputs and analytical workflows Mindset & AttributesStrong business acumen and curiosity about enterprise transformation and key trends impacting this (e.g. AI Operating Models)Comfortable working in fast-paced, client-facing environmentsAbility to collaborate across sales, strategy, services and product teamsHigh ownership mentality with a growth mindset\nEducationMaster’s degree preference or equivalent executive experience in business, economics, finance, informatics, technology\nOtherFluent English required; additional European languages a strong advantage - with German and / or French language skills particularly attractiveWillingness to travel regionally\nWhy This RoleDirect exposure to executive transformation discussions across major European enterprisesOpportunity to shape a regional transformation motionApply consulting skillset in a high-impact enterprise SaaS contextWork on complex strategy and operating model challenges across industriesCollaborate with experienced practitioners across strategy, transformation, and technology domains\nBenefits at Planview\nAt Planview, you’ll join our global team and culture which reflects the vibrant communities in which our employees live and work. To support you at Planview, you will enjoy:Unplugged Days: 4 company-wide paid days off per year to recharge and relax.Generous PTO offerings (region dependent).Region specific competitive benefit plans to support you at any life stage including parental leave, retirement, medical plans, wellness support, and remote work support.Paid time to volunteer through Planview’s Force for Good Week.Employee Referral bonus program.Weekly office lunches for hybrid team members and social events.Flexible work hours/environment.Now is a great time to join our team. If you are looking for a place to grow your career, innovate with best-in-class solutions, and build the future of connected work, Planview is the right place for you!\nDiversity, Equity and Inclusion at Planview\nAs part of our efforts to build a workforce with diverse talent, we encourage applications from Indigenous, Black, and other racialized communities, 2SLGBTQIA+ communities, people with neurodivergence, immigrants, people with disabilities, and other equity deserving groups. In addition to building a diverse workforce, we are committed to fostering an inclusive and accessible experience. Reasonable accommodations for the interview process can be requested by emailing recruitment@planview.com."}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4403208078","title":"Solution Engineer  (Pre-sales)- Identity Governance and Administration (IGA)","company":"One Identity","location":"Aliso Viejo","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://fr.linkedin.com/jobs/view/solution-engineer-pre-sales-identity-governance-and-administration-iga-at-one-identity-4403208078?position=58&pageNum=0&refId=XpAiGCPEM7yX1Qav3JJGmw%3D%3D&trackingId=i4nJJnUrE88lnu%2FSRvK5rQ%3D%3D","description":"We Are Hiring!One Identity is looking for an experienced Presales Solution Engineer  in France. The Solution Engineer will interact with our customers and partners across EMEA, with a focus on France, for our IGA Product (One Identity Manager) . This role will require you to provide product demonstrations, support the sales team on calls, work on proof of concepts, deliver presentations, and travel to customers and/or partners as necessary.The Solution Engineer will work alongside their colleagues, participate in further strengthening our team culture, and support the sales team to create solutions for prospects and customers. The Solution Engineer will act as a trusted advisor to our customers while aiding the customer’s transformational journey.To accomplish this, you should have a strong desire to set the vision, translating business objectives into enticing and actionable recommendations.ResponsibilitiesLead the technical discovery and qualification process of early opportunities, helping to uncover prospects/customers’ current pains and align with their business objectives.Lead the technical elements within the sales cycle. This may include being part of the design, delivery and support of a technical proof of concept; creating technical proposals; responding to RFP/RFIs/Security Questionnaires/Technical Response Documents; attending sales meetings; leading workshops and providing technical expertise to demonstrate the One Identity products as an SME.Collaborate with Product Management to provide consistent and actionable feedback based on customer interactions. You must be able to communicate effectively with Support, Engineering, Product Managers, Product Marketing Managers, Sales, and other stakeholders.Partner with Product Marketing to help develop assets, knowledge base content and deliver training sessions to improve technical product knowledge of existing features to both customers and Account Executives.Contribute to the success of a rapidly growing and evolving SE organisation.Be involved in contributing to & maintaining a central knowledge repository to answer technical product questions during the RFP/RFI process.Stay abreast of the latest developments in Digital Identity.Help onboard and enable partners with One Identity solutions.QualificationsAt least 5 years of Technical Solution EngineeringPresales experience preferred Customer orientation and excellent communication skills ( in English and French )are essential .Experience deploying, managing and configuring SaaS, Hybrid and On-Premise solutions within the IAM space, particularly IGA products (e.g. Sailpoint, Saviynt, Cyberark, Okta, Oracle Identity Manager and similar).A good working understanding of SaaS, Hybrid and On-Premise deployment methodologies, with a strong foundation in SaaS.Familiar with core web technologies: Ruby on Rails, Angular, Python, PHP, HTML/CSS, REST, and others.Thorough understanding of the IT industry, competitive landscape and key technologies.Knowledge of cybersecurity practices in protecting systems, networks and digital identities.An understanding of core security concerns within a typical application.Familiar with the Digital Identity space and eager to learn more.Familiar with enterprise level directory deployments and configurations.Excellent written and verbal communication skills; a knack for delivering compelling presentations and product demonstrations to either external customers or internal teams.\nCompany DescriptionOne Identity enables organizations of all sizes to better secure, manage, monitor, protect, and analyze information and infrastructure to help fuel innovation and drive their businesses forward. With team members around the globe, we intend to continue to grow revenues and add value to customers.When you join our team, you will have the opportunity to build and develop products at a scale few others can provide. Our product portfolio serves a large base of customers and we are addressing the strategic imperatives for enterprise businesses. Working with some of the most talented employees the industry has to offer, we provide enhanced career opportunities for team members to learn and grow in a rapidly changing environment.\nWhy Work With Us?Life at One Identity means collaborating with dedicated professionals with a passion for technology.When we see something that could be improved, we get to work inventing the solution.Our people demonstrate our winning culture through positive and meaningful relationships.We invest in our people and offer a series of programs that enables them to pursue a career that fulfils their potential.Our team members’ health and wellness is our priority as well as rewarding them for their hard work.One Identity is an Equal Opportunity Employer and Prohibits Discrimination and Harassment of Any Kind. One Identity is committed to the principle of equal employment opportunity for all employees and to providing employees with a work environment free of discrimination and harassment. All employment decisions at One Identity are based on business needs, job requirements and individual qualifications, without regard to race, colour, religion or belief, national, social or ethnic origin, sex (including pregnancy), age, physical, mental or sensory disability, HIV status, sexual orientation, gender identity and/or expression, marital, civil union or domestic partnership status, past or present military service, family medical history or genetic information, family or parental status, or any other status protected by the laws or regulations in the locations where we operate. One Identity will not tolerate discrimination or harassment based on any of these characteristics. One Identity encourages applicants of all ages.Come join us.For more information, visit us on the web at One Identity Careers | Explore Opportunities with the OI Team.Important Notice for Job SeekersJob seekers should be aware of fraudulent job offers from online scammers and only apply to roles listed on quest.com/careers using our applicant system. Note: We do not use text messaging or third‑party messaging apps like Telegram to communicate with applicants. Please only interact with people claiming to be Quest employees if they have an email address ending in @quest.com or @oneidentity.com."}
