{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4405267026","title":"Solutions Consultant","company":"Poka Inc.","location":"Quebec","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://grnh.se/b9qjm58r4us","description":"At Poka, we’re transforming how frontline teams operate, learn, and solve problems.\n\nOur connected worker platform is purpose-built for manufacturing, empowering frontline workers to share knowledge, collaborate in real-time, and drive continuous improvement. Think of it as the missing digital link, bringing the human interface into the stack of the Smart Factory, generating the right data and insights that drive entirely new scales of process improvements.\n\nWe’re proud to support global leaders like Nestlé, Bosch, Mars, and Danone in their digital transformation journeys and as part of the IFS family, our reach and impact continue to grow globally.\n\nIf you’ve lived the realities of manufacturing - and know how to translate operational challenges into compelling technical solutions - this role is built for you.\n\nWe’re looking for a Solutions Consultant who combines hands-on manufacturing knowledge with pre-sales expertise. Whether you’ve sold technical solutions into factories or transitioned from the plant floor into a customer-facing solutions role, you understand both the operational complexity and the consultative process required to drive digital transformation.\n\nYou’ll be a key partner to Sales, guiding prospects through how Poka unlocks measurable value across operations, frontline enablement, and continuous improvement initiatives.\n\nWhat you’ll be doing\n\nAct as a trusted advisor to manufacturing leaders, deeply understanding their operational processes, pain points, and digital maturity.Lead consultative discovery conversations that connect real-world manufacturing challenges to Poka’s connected worker capabilities.Design and deliver tailored product demonstrations that clearly articulate business impact, from waste reduction and standardized work to training optimization and knowledge capture.Architect solution frameworks that support enterprise-level manufacturing environments, ensuring alignment with IT, OT, and operational requirements.Develop compelling value narratives and business cases grounded in Lean, Continuous Improvement, and operational excellence principles.Partner closely with Sales to support strategic deals, RFPs, PoCs, and executive presentations.Contribute manufacturing expertise to the broader Solutions team, helping elevate demo strategy, storytelling, and use-case positioning.Represent Poka at customer-facing events, plant visits, and strategic workshops.\n\nWhat you bring\n\nMinimum 2 years of experience in a pre-sales, solutions consulting, or technical sales role supporting manufacturing customers.Plus either:5+ years of hands-on manufacturing experience (operations, engineering, CI, production leadership), or5+ years selling or supporting technical solutions into manufacturing environments.Strong understanding of Lean Manufacturing, Continuous Improvement, standardized work, and operational KPIs.Experience delivering customized product demonstrations and leading technical discussions with both operational and IT stakeholders.Ability to translate complex technical capabilities into clear operational outcomes and business value.Strong communication skills with the confidence to engage plant managers, CI leaders, IT teams, and executives.Experience contributing to PoCs, solution design, or technical validation processes.Fluency in English and French.Willingness to travel (up to 30%)\nWhy Poka?\n\nAt Poka, you won’t just demo software - you’ll help shape how global manufacturers empower their frontline teams.\n\nYou’ll work at the intersection of manufacturing, technology, and AI-driven innovation, helping industry leaders modernize operations and unlock smarter ways of working. As part of a fast-growing company within the IFS ecosystem, you’ll have global exposure, strong collaboration across regions, and real influence on how we position and evolve our solutions.\n\nIf you’re ready to combine manufacturing expertise with consultative selling - and make a tangible impact on factory floors around the world - we’d love to meet you.\n\nWhat we offer:\n\nDynamic and collaborative work environment.Generous vacation policy upon arrival.Remote work policy.A truly flexible schedule that allows you to adapt your work hours.Benefits Plan offered from day one.MacBook Pro and €500 allowance for your home office.Generous referral bonus.The tools, support, and opportunities you need to keep learning and progressing in your career.\n\nWant to learn more about our culture? Click HERE.\n\nPlease note: An understanding of English is essential at Poka, as it is the language used during company-wide meetings and many internal communications, ensuring effective collaboration and decision-making. In addition, as Poka operates in an international environment, English is the primary language for communicating with our clients and partners, enabling us to better serve them and represent Poka in a professional manner."}
