{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4384879830","title":"(Senior) Account Manager (m/f/d) - Machinery Mfg and Sales Area Management","company":"Emerson","location":"St Louis","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://hdjq.fa.us2.oraclecloud.com/hcmUI/CandidateExperience/en/job/26002275/?utm_medium=jobboard&utm_source=linkedin","description":"Job Description\n\nThe Hybrid Account and Sales Area Manager (SAM) is a proactive individual contributor with a focus on boosting revenue growth and nurturing customer success throughout a specific territory within France, as well as driving growth, shape customer relationships, and work across a cross-functional team to execute account plans that expand Emerson’s footprint in key industries such as Electrical Machinery. This position involves thoughtful planning, effective implementation, and working closely with NI resources, distributors, and solution & integration partners. The Hybrid SAM will lead the development and execution of a comprehensive growth plan, using both direct and indirect sales channels to expand NI’s market presence and grow top tiers account. This position reports directly to the Regional Sales Manager.\n\nIn This Role, Your Responsibilities Will Be:\n\n Drive Customer Growth & Strategic Execution  Develop and execute creative, high-impact account strategies and account plans that consistently generate strong (double-digit) growth.  Identify and articulate Emerson T&M’s differentiated value to influence technical and business decisionmakers at multiple levels.  Lead customer engagements through platform discussions, strategic consulting, and technical conversations on innovative test technologies.  Lead Account Team Collaboration  Drive a coordinated, company-wide strategy through collaboration with: Engineering & Technical Consultants  Business Development Managers  Marketing teams  Partners and Channel Ecosystem  Transportation & Portfolio Business Units  Coach and influence cross-functional