ew global, regional, and national accounts in the QSR industry segmentDesign and implement strategic business plans for national accountsPresent value-add products and programs, highlighting impact to the customer’s businessEnsure customer service delivery emphasizing the delivery of Ecolab's value propositionPartner and lead service and sales teams to ensure that revenue and profit targets are met and delivery of Service Standards are consistentLook for more business opportunities from potential and current accounts to achieve annual sales and profit budget while retaining the existing corporate accountsUnderstand all Ecolab solutions available and strive for Ecolab total solution across all of the customers restaurant locations for both current and prospect customersMaintain contacts within industry groups and bodies to network and identify new opportunities and stay ahead of changesDrive teamwork in order to deliver the value of EcolabEstablish and maintain routine communications with regional and global CAMs that have alignments to same Global Corporate AccountsLead project teams consisting of account manager/ regional manager and cross divisional partners to sell and maintain corporate accountsComply with company’s policies in order to ensure high quality of sales and serviceStrictly adhere to the Code of Conduct policyEnsure full compliance with all applicable regulatory and corporate standardsMaintain up to date knowledge of the company’s new products, programs and equipment, and industry knowledge\n\nPosition Details\n\nCandidate must reside in: UAE or KSATerritory will include: MEA50% overnight travel required\n\nMinimum Qualifications\n\nBachelor's Degree or equivalent combination of education and experience 10+ years of sales experience and a proven track record of deals larger than USD 500K.Established industry/customer relationships at decision making and executive levelsMust have a valid Driver's License and acceptable Motor Vehicle RecordFluent in English\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\n5-7 years of Quick Service Restaurant industry experience & knowledgeSpecialty chemical industry experienceDemonstrated large account management success in selected industry with executive-level relationship sales experienceFinancial and analytical skills, including the understanding of a P&L and the financial implications of customers situations and concerns\n\nAbout Ecolab’s Quick Service Restaurant Division\n\nLearn how we help 200,000 quick-service restaurants around the world with focused products and programs to improve their guest experience, lower operating costs, drive revenue growth and safeguard customer trust. Through our Kay Chemical business, we fulfill the cleaning and sanitization needs of a niche customer segment through customized offerings, service, support and training. Help us leverage our solutions and expertise to ensure food safety and brand consistency across the biggest limited-service and fast-casual restaurants in the world.\n\nNuestro compromiso con una cultura de inclusión y pertenencia\n\nEcolab está comprometido con el trato justo e igualitario de todas las personas colaboradoras y postulantes, y con la promoción de los principios de igualdad de oportunidades en el empleo. Reclutaremos, contrataremos, promoveremos, transferiremos y brindaremos oportunidades de desarrollo con base en las calificaciones individuales y el desempeño laboral, en todos los aspectos relacionados con el empleo, la compensación, los beneficios, las condiciones laborales y las oportunidades de crecimiento. Ecolab no discriminará a ninguna persona colaboradora ni postulante por motivos de raza, religión, color, credo, nacionalidad, estado de ciudadanía, sexo, orientación sexual, identidad y expresión de género, información genética, estado civil, edad o discapacidad."}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4404117106","title":"Senior AI Engineer (LLMs & Knowledge Graphs)","company":"Jimmy Technologies","location":"Sheridan","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://jobs.fromjimmy.com/o/senior-ai-engineer-llms-knowledge-graphs","description":"OverviewOur client, a Fortune 50 leader in enterprise solutions and innovations, is seeking a Senior AI Engineer with Knowledge Graphs and LLMs skills to join their AI incubator to scout, incubate, and validate internal ideas. This role is part of a high-impact strategy leveraging Graph Neural Networks (GNNs) and Generative AI to redefine workflows, semantic search, and intelligence for enterprise solutions in Finance, Operations, Supply Chain, Engineering, or Investments.\nThis is a remote-first position with a required overlap of US working hours (2-6 PM CET).\nRole & ResponsibilitiesAs a Senior AI Engineer, you will:Build Agentic Workflows: Implement orchestration, retrieval pipelines, and validator agents using graph-aware tools.Optimize Retrieval: Build hybrid search pipelines (lexical + vector) and integrate vector databases like FAISS, Milvus, or Pinecone.Model Integration: Integrate LLMs (Azure OpenAI, Anthropic) and support domain-specific fine-tuning or adapter models.Scalable Engineering: Develop robust API endpoints and ETL pipelines to support model and agent runtimes.Experiment & Evaluate: Create evaluation suites for reliability, drift detection, and performance optimization.\nRequired Skills & ExperiencePython Expertise: 3-6+ years of strong Python engineering experience.Core ML & Experimental Design: Strong grounding in machine learning and deep learning fundamentals with the ability to design experiments, evaluate model robustness, and mitigate bias.Graph Intelligence: Depth in Graph Theory, Knowledge Graph modeling, and GNNs.Modern AI Patterns: Hands-on experience with RAG, Agentic frameworks, and Prompt Engineering.Data Engineering: Proficiency in building data pipelines, chunking strategies, and handling large datasets.Cloud & Deployment: Experience with AWS/Azure/GCP and CI/CD workflows.Engineering Discipline: Strong Git discipline, unit testing, and agile pod experience.Excellent problem-solving skills and keen attention to detail.Ability to participate in the discussions and lead the technical discussionsHave a consultancy mindset → always try to find a solution for the clientMake decisions about the solution and design\nWork ConditionsStart Date: ASAPLocation: Remote (99%); must be able to travel freely within Europe for workshops.US Time Zone Overlap: Required (2 PM - 6 PM CET)Rate: 300-340 EUR/MD\nIf you are passionate about AI, Graph-centric AI, Python, and building next-generation agentic workflows, this role with our client offers an exciting opportunity to work on cutting-edge R&D projects!"}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4407562557","title":"Haemato-Oncology Medical Scientific Liaison (MSL)","company":"GSK","location":"London","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://jobs.gsk.com/jobs/439364?lang=en-us&source=LinkedIn","description":"Site Name: Jeddah Headquarters Business Park, Riyadh Olaya Towers\n\nPosted Date: Apr 28 2026\n\nWe manufacture and supply reliable, high-quality medicines and vaccines to meet patients’ needs and drive our performance. Our network of 37 medicines and vaccines manufacturing sites delivered 1.7 billion packs of medicines and 409 million vaccine doses in 2024 to help make a positive impact on the health of millions of people. Our supply chain is not just core to our operations; it’s vital to bringing our innovations to patients as quickly, efficiently and effectively as possible. Technology is transforming how we manufacture medicines and vaccines, enabling us to increase the speed, quality and scale of product supply. We need the very best minds and capability to help us on our journey to make more complex products, harnessing the power of smart manufacturing technologies including robotics, digital solutions and artificial intelligence to deliver for patients.\n\nHaemato-Oncology Medical Scientific Liaison\n\nYou will be a field-based Haemato-Oncology Medical Scientific Liaison supporting medical engagement across Saudi Arabia. You will build trusted, scientific relationships with haematology and oncology experts. You will gather and share medical insights to shape evidence generation and medical strategy. We value clear communicators who work well across teams and who are motivated by making a real difference for patients. This role offers growth through exposure to clinical development, cross-functional projects, and opportunities to influence care in line with GSK’s mission to unite science, technology and talent to get ahead of disease together. The Medical Scientific Liaison (MSL) is a non-promotional field-based medical role responsible for conducting medical engagements/activities that ensure the safe and effective use of GSK’s medicines while generating medical insights. MSL is expected to drive EEs/HCPs education journeys using the behavior adoption tool, provide support to GSK clinical development & Key Evidence Generation programs.\n\nResponsibilities:\n\nThis role will provide YOU the opportunity to lead key activities to progress YOUR career. These responsibilities include some of the following:\n\n\n Conduct peer-to-peer scientific interactions with haemato and oncology healthcare professionals, both proactively and reactively. Capture, document and share medical insights to inform local evidence generation and medical strategy. Support medical education activities, advisory boards, and scientific workshops for external experts and internal colleagues. Provide timely, fair and evidence-based responses to unsolicited medical information requests and safety queries. Support clinical development activities such as investigator identification and site feasibility when required. Use approved systems to record activities and outcomes, and ensure compliance with local laws, policies and pharmacovigilance requirements.\n\n\nWhy You?\n\nBasic Qualification\n\nWe are seeking professionals with the following required skills and qualifications to help us achieve our goals:\n\n\n Bachelor’s degree in pharmaceutical science. Saudi National Valid license from the Saudi Commission for Health Specialties or equivalent local licensure. At least 2 years’ experience in pharmaceutical medical, clinical, or field roles. Practical knowledge of haemato-oncology clinical practice or experience working with oncology or haematology healthcare professionals. Strong written and spoken English. Arabic is an advantage. Excellent communication skills and experience presenting clinical data to healthcare audiences.\n\n\nPreferred Qualification\n\nIf you have the following characteristics, it would be a plus\n\n\n Advanced degree ( PhD, or MSc) or postgraduate training in hematology, oncology, or related area. Experience supporting clinical trials, investigator identification, or site engagement. Familiarity with medical information systems and CRM platforms. Experience in evidence generation, publications, or health economics and outcomes research. Experience working within a matrix environment and collaborating with commercial, access, and regulatory teams. Fluency in Arabic and experience engaging national stakeholders, payers or guideline committees.\n\n\nWork Model\n\nThis role will be based in Saudi Arabia and is field-based with regular travel across the assigned geography. The role is on-site and hybrid working arrangements may be agreed based on business needs and local policy.\n\nHow to apply\n\nIf this role speaks to your skills and goals, we encourage you to apply. Tell us how your experience in haemato-oncology and scientific engagement will help patients and teams succeed. We look forward to hearing from you.\n\nنقوم بتصنيع وتوريد أدوية ولقاحات موثوقة وعالية الجودة لتلبية احتياجات المرضى وتعزيز أدائنا. سلَّمت شبكتنا المكوّنة من 37 موقعًا لإنتاج الأدوية واللقاحات ما مجموعه 1.7 مليار عبوة أدوية و409 مليون جرعة لقاح في عام 2024، مساهمةً في تحقيق أثر إيجابي على صحة ملايين الأشخاص. سلسلة التوريد لدينا ليست مجرد عنصر أساسي في عملياتنا؛ بل هي حيوية لإيصال ابتكاراتنا إلى المرضى بأسرع شكل ممكن وبكفاءة وفاعلية. تعمل التكنولوجيا على تحويل طريقة تصنيع الأدوية واللقاحات، مما يتيح لنا زيادة سرعة وجودة وحجم التوريد. نحتاج أفضل العقول والقدرات لمساندتنا في رحلتنا نحو تصنيع منتجات أكثر تعقيدًا، مستفيدين من قوة تقنيات التصنيع الذكي بما في ذلك الروبوتات، والحلول الرقمية، والذكاء الاصطناعي لخدمة المرضى.\n\nمنسق علمي طبي — أمراض الدم والأورام (Haemato‑Oncology Medical Scientific Liaison)\n\nستكون منسقًا علميًا طبيًا ميدانيًا في مجال أمراض الدم والأورام، تدعم التواصل الطبي عبر المملكة العربية السعودية. ستبني علاقات علمية موثوقة مع خبراء أمراض الدم والأورام، وستجمع وتشارك الرؤى الطبية للمساهمة في تشكيل جهود توليد الأدلة والاستراتيجية الطبية. نُقدّر أصحاب التواصل الواضح الذين يعملون بفاعلية عبر الفرق والذين يتحفّزون لإحداث فرق حقيقي للمرضى. يوفر هذا الدور فرصًا للنمو من خلال التعرض لتطوير الدراسات السريرية، المشاريع متعددة التخصصات، وفرص التأثير على الرعاية بما يتماشى مع مهمة GSK في توحيد العلم والتكنولوجيا والمواهب للتقدّم على الأمراض معًا.\n\nالمسؤوليات\n\nيوفر هذا الدور لك الفرصة لقيادة أنشطة رئيسية لتطوير مسارك المهني. تشمل بعض المسؤوليات ما يلي:\n\n\nإجراء تفاعلات علمية بين النظراء مع مختصي أمراض الدم والأورام، بشكل استباقي واستجابي.جمع وتوثيق ومشاركة الرؤى الطبية لإثراء جهود توليد الأدلة المحلية والاستراتيجية الطبية.دعم أنشطة التعليم الطبي، مجالس الاستشارة (advisory boards)، وورش العمل العلمية للخبراء الخارجيين والزملاء الداخليين.تقديم ردود مبنية على الأدلة وفي الوقت المناسب على طلبات المعلومات الطبية غير الموجّهة واستفسارات السلامة.دعم أنشطة التطوير السريري مثل تحديد المحققين ودراسة جدوى المواقع عند الحاجة.استخدام الأنظمة المعتمدة لتسجيل الأنشطة والنتائج، وضمان الامتثال للقوانين المحلية والسياسات ومتطلبات اليقظة الدوائية (Pharmacovigilance).\n\n\nلماذا أنت؟\n\nالمؤهلات الأساسية نبحث عن محترفين يمتلكون المهارات والمؤهلات التالية لمساعدتنا في تحقيق أهدافنا:\n\n\nالصيدلة.ترخيص ساري من الهيئة السعودية للتخصصات الصحية.خبرة لا تقل عن سنتين في أدوار طبية أو سريرية أو ميدانية في قطاع الأدوية.معرفة عملية بممارسات الرعاية السريرية في أمراض الدم والأورام أو خبرة في العمل مع مختصي الأورام أو أمراض الدم.إجادة قوية للغة الإنجليزية كتابةً ومحادثة؛ تُعتبر اللغة العربية ميزة.مهارات تواصل ممتازة وخبرة في عرض البيانات السريرية أمام جمهور من المتخصصين في الرعاية الصحية.\n\n\nالمؤهلات المفضلة\n\nإن توافرت لديك الخصائص التالية فستكون ميزة:\n\n\nشهادة متقدمة أو تدريب متخصص في أمراض الدم أو الأورام أو مجال ذي صلة.خبرة في دعم التجارب السريرية، تحديد المحققين أو التواصل مع مواقع البحث.إلمام بأنظمة المعلومات الطبية ومنصات إدارة علاقات العملاء (CRM).خبرة في توليد الأدلة، النشر العلمي، أو أبحاث اقتصاديات الصحة ونتائج الرعاية.خبرة العمل ضمن بيئة مصفوفية والتعاون مع فرق تجارية، فرق الوصول (access) والجهات التنظيمية.إجادة اللغة العربية وخبرة في التواصل مع أصحاب المصلحة الوطنيين أو دافعي التكلفة أو لجان وضع الإرشادات.\n\n\nنموذج العمل\n\nسيكون هذا الدور ميدانيًا ومقرّه المملكة العربية السعودية، ويتطلب سفرًا منتظمًا ضمن المنطقة المخصصة. الدور يتطلب تواجدًا ميدانيًا، ويمكن الاتفاق على ترتيبات عمل هجينة حسب احتياجات العمل والسياسة المحلية.\n\nكيفية التقديم\n\nإذا كان هذا الدور يتوافق مع مهاراتك وأهدافك، نشجعك على التقديم. أخبرنا كيف ستسهم خبرتك في أمراض الدم والأورام والتواصل العلمي في دعم المرضى والفرق على النجاح. نتطلع لسماعك.\n\nWhy GSK?\n\nUniting science, technology and talent to get ahead of disease together.\n\nGSK is a global biopharma company with a purpose to unite science, technology and talent to get ahead of disease together. We aim to positively impact the health of 2.5 billion people by the end of the decade, as a successful, growing company where people can thrive. We get ahead of disease by preventing and treating it with innovation in specialty medicines and vaccines. We focus on four therapeutic areas: respiratory, immunology and inflammation; oncology; HIV; and infectious diseases – to impact health at scale.\n\nPeople and patients around the world count on the medicines and vaccines we make, so we’re committed to creating an environment where our people can thrive and focus on what matters most. Our culture of being ambitious for patients, accountable for impact and doing the right thing is the foundation for how, together, we deliver for patients, shareholders and our people.\n\nContact information:\n\nYou may apply for this position online by selecting the Apply now button.\n\nImportant notice to Employment businesses/ Agencies\n\nGSK does not accept referrals from employment businesses and/or employment agencies in respect of the vacancies posted on this site. All employment businesses/agencies are required to contact GSK's commercial and general procurement/human resources department to obtain prior written authorization before referring any candidates to GSK. The obtaining of prior written authorization is a condition precedent to any agreement (verbal or written) between the employment business/ agency and GSK. In the absence of such written authorization being obtained any actions undertaken by the employment business/agency shall be deemed to have been performed without the consent or contractual agreement of GSK. GSK shall therefore not be liable for any fees arising from such actions or any fees arising from any referrals by employment businesses/agencies in respect of the vacancies posted on this site.\n\n"}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4406879122","title":"Solution Deployment Manager","company":"360Learning","location":"New York","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://jobs.lever.co/360learning/0dba50d1-52f4-4114-8421-2f9e19210fde/apply?source=LinkedIn","description":"As our Solution Deployment Manager, you are part of our Implementation team, which plays a key role in onboarding seamlessly new customers: they are working cross department (Sales, Product and Customer Success) to understand and document client use cases and requirements and then translate them into set up and configuration of the 360Learning platform.\n\nYou will manage all phases of the implementation lifecycle, from sales turnover and kick off to handover to support. You will drive project management, define 360Learning platform architecture for our clients, facilitate integrations (flat files, API’s) and 3rd party apps, guide and provide assistance in order to ensure the successful deployment of their platform.\n\nIn addition, you will follow your customers' portfolio along their contract to increase product adoption, as well as to deliver Solutions complementary to the Product like platform audits.\n\nWithin 1 month, you will:\n\nBecome a Trello expert through our onboarding processUnderstand our product offering through trainingMaster our platform and be able to support clients on basics requests through ticketing\n\nWithin 3 months, you will:\n\nStart to onboard your own new clients Drive project management in order to ensure successful platform deployment from Kick-off meeting, regular touchpoints until handover to supportHost functional and technical workshops with clients to support them in their platform customization and structuring\n\nWithin 6 months, you will:\n\nSuccessfully ensure 360Learning platform deployment for new clientsSuccessfully implement integration (SSO, third-party tools), deliver technical expertise on how to integrate their learning platform to their t