gn content with paid ads strategy and campaign objectivesSupport sales and client-facing teams with strong content direction4. Execution OversightOversee content across:Social mediaPaid ads (Meta, TikTok, Google)E-commerce stores (product pages, descriptions)Landing pages & funnelsEmail marketing\nRequirements4–7+ years of experience in content marketing, with at least: 2+ years in a leadership or team lead role in a marketing agency.Proven experience in a marketing agency environmentStrong background in e-commerce content & conversion-driven copywritingExperience managing and scaling a content teamDeep understanding of performance marketingFluent in English (mandatory), Arabic is a plus\nNice to HaveExperience in KSA/GCC marketFamiliarity with Shopify, GA4, Meta Ads ManagerExperience using AI tools (ChatGPT, etc.) to scale content production"}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4406188516","title":"Country Manager","company":"Narwhal Labs","location":"Bristol","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://sa.linkedin.com/jobs/view/country-manager-at-narwhal-labs-4406188516?position=1&pageNum=0&refId=lRMZB31aWA2DsqypRP%2FSaw%3D%3D&trackingId=SY%2BjVS%2FF85LtZ%2FMj4qJjSw%3D%3D","description":"📍 Saudi Arabia💼 Full-time💰 up to SAR 510,000 DOE\nAbout DeepBlue OS:DeepBlue OS is the Agentic AI Operating System built in Bristol. We run autonomous voice, SMS, email and WhatsApp communications for enterprise customers — deterministic, auditable, and built for regulated industries. Our Glass Box Architecture is what enterprise buys; our pricing is what SMBs need.In 2026 we're rolling internationally. Tier 1 markets are Ireland, Australia, UAE, and Saudi Arabia. The Country Manager is the first and only DeepBlue hire in-market — a solo operator who owns the full commercial picture, supported by the Global GTM Lead in Bristol.\nThe role:This is a builder role, not a manager role. The Country Manager owns one market's P&L from day one: partner acquisition, agency network, revenue, and market intelligence. There is no in-country team — full team setup follows only after market traction is proven at the 6-month gate. The Country Manager reports directly to the Global GTM Lead.The entry model is Deel EOR on Day 1. At month 6, if commercial gates are met, Narwhal incorporates a local entity and opens a Regus office. The Country Manager transitions from solo operator to team lead at that point.\nThe Narwhal expansion playbookIdentify — pick the one anchor partner whose distribution gives you bulk account volume (telco, MSP, trades platform).Prove — land them, white-label DeepBlue OS under their brand, process real volume.Scale — layer 5–10 local agencies on top of the anchor, open direct sign-ups, build vertical case studies.Move — hand the steady-state to a scaled team, take the learnings to the next vertical or country.\nWhat you ownRevenue for your market — from day one, with uncapped accelerators on channel revenueAnchor partner acquisition — the one deal that makes the whole market viable. You identify, qualify, pitch, and close it soloLocal agency network — recruited, enabled, and supported. 5–10 agencies operating by month 12Market intelligence — regulation, competition, partner moves — fed back to the Global GTM Lead weekly via Close CRM and SlackIn-country presence — trade events, industry associations, press, private C-suite dinners. You are DeepBlue in Saudi Arabia6-month gate readiness — you own all the conditions that determine whether Narwhal commits to a permanent entity and office\nWho we're looking for\nEssential8–12 years B2B channel or enterprise sales in your target marketDeep network at Director level or above inside one of: the dominant telco, a major trades/services platform, or a leading MSPProven track record closing 6- and 7-figure partnerships — not account managementSelf-directed solo operator — comfortable with a remote HQ and no in-country support teamCommercially sharp: unit economics, pricing models, building a business case for a technical product\nAdvantageousExperience in AI, SaaS, communications technology, or platform/marketplace businessesExperience with white-label or channel distribution modelsTrack record building a market from scratch, not inheriting an established territory\nMarket-specific requirementsSaudi Arabia — Native or fluent Arabic is essential — not optional. Deep KSA relationships at Director+ level inside STC, Mobily, or a top-10 Saudi services platform. Existing iqama/residency strongly preferred. Majlis rhythm and relationship-first long sales cycles is non-negotiable.\nWhat you getUncapped commission on partner and channel revenue, with accelerators on volume milestonesFull DeepBlue OS product training and Bristol onboarding in week oneQuarterly travel to Bristol HQ for SLT leadership offsites — flights and accommodation coveredClose CRM access, Cognism B2B data, and the full Bristol commercial infrastructure from day oneDirect line to the Global GTM Lead and CEO — no middle management\nWe don't run long recruitment processes. If you're right for this role, you'll speak to the Global GTM Lead within five working days. No recruiters - thank you."}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4406905865","title":"Director of Business Development (Global / MENA Focus)","company":"UNLOCKLAND","location":"San Francisco","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://sa.linkedin.com/jobs/view/director-of-business-development-global-mena-focus-at-unlockland-4406905865?position=2&pageNum=0&refId=lRMZB31aWA2DsqypRP%2FSaw%3D%3D&trackingId=smmnSz5%2Bkek3jUvCTmhqeA%3D%3D","description":"UnlockLand is an AI-driven PropTech company recognized as one of the top innovators in the “Future of Lifestyle” PropTech Accelerator, led by the National Information Technology Development Program (NITDP) and the Real Estate General Authority (REGA) under Saudi Vision 2030.\n Our mission is to transform how developers, investors, and governments plan, evaluate, and optimize real-estate assets. \nUnlockLand’s AI Operating System integrates geospatial data, financial modelling, and regulatory intelligence to deliver instant feasibility studies and predictive analytics — helping cities and investors build smarter, more sustainable communities.\nRole SummaryAs Director of Business Development, you will lead enterprise and government growth for UnlockLand—owning the full commercial lifecycle from strategic outreach to signed partnerships and long-term expansion. You will build a high-quality pipeline across developers, institutional investors, ministries, planning authorities, and large-scale real estate programs, and translate market demand into actionable product and go-to-market priorities.\nKey Responsibilities (Elaborated)1. Enterprise & Government Revenue GrowthOwn and scale UnlockLand’s revenue pipeline across enterprise clients and public-sector stakeholders.Build relationships with developers, investors, REITs, consultants, and government entities to drive platform adoption.Lead complex, multi-stakeholder deal cycles from discovery to negotiation, contracting, and close.2. Strategic Partnerships & National ProgramsIdentify and structure partnerships with ministries, regulators, planning authorities, accelerators, and strategic ecosystem players.Develop partnership frameworks for pilots, city-scale deployments, and nationwide initiatives aligned with Vision 2030 objectives.Coordinate proposal development, MoUs, and commercial agreements with government and enterprise counterparts.3. Go-To-Market Strategy & Market ExpansionBuild and execute GTM plans for priority regions and sectors (e.g., residential, mixed-use, infrastructure, industrial).Develop segmentation strategies, ICPs, and value propositions tailored to different buyer types (developers vs. ministries vs. institutional capital).Create scalable playbooks for entering new markets, including pricing assumptions, implementation pathways, and success metrics.4. Product Commercialization & Solution SellingTranslate client needs into product requirements—helping shape modules around feasibility, zoning/regulatory intelligence, and predictive analytics.Run high-impact product demos and executive workshops that quantify ROI (time saved, risk reduction, capital efficiency).Package offerings into clear solution tiers (pilot → enterprise → national deployment) with measurable outcomes.5. Pipeline Management & Performance ExecutionBuild forecasting discipline: maintain CRM hygiene, pipeline velocity tracking, and conversion improvement.Define commercial KPIs (meetings, qualified pipeline, win rate, ACV, sales cycle, renewal/expansion).Partner with Marketing to drive demand generation through events, thought leadership, and targeted ABM.6. Executive Stakeholder ManagementWork closely with the CEO and leadership team on strategic accounts, board-level opportunities, and investor-facing growth narratives.Represent UnlockLand at industry forums, government meetings, and innovation summits as a trusted commercial leader.Support partnership governance post-close to ensure adoption, renewals, and expansion.\nIdeal ProfileThe ideal Director of Business Development is a strategic, relationship-driven commercial leader with:8–15+ years in business development, enterprise sales, partnerships, or GTM leadership (PropTech, real estate, SaaS, AI, fintech, or infrastructure).Proven success closing complex enterprise and/or public-sector deals with multiple stakeholders and long sales cycles.Strong familiarity with real estate development economics (feasibility, entitlements, underwriting, capital stacks) and the workflows of developers/investors.Experience engaging ministries, regulators, planning authorities, or national transformation programs (Vision 2030 experience is a major plus).Ability to sell technical platforms with clarity—communicating product value to both executives and technical stakeholders.A builder mindset: comfortable creating playbooks, partnerships, pricing, packaging, and repeatable growth systems from scratch.Passion for AI-driven transformation, smarter cities, and scaling real estate intelligence globally.\nWhat Success Looks Like (First 6–12 Months)Build a prioritized pipeline of high-value enterprise and government opportunities.Close landmark partnerships (pilot + enterprise contract structure) and establish repeatable pathways for expansion.Implement a scalable BD operating system: CRM process, pipeline reporting, and GTM playbooks.Establish UnlockLand as a trusted partner in AI-enabled planning and feasibility for developers and governments.\n"}
{"source":"linkedin","source_id":"4405555520","title":"HNW Network Connector - Saudi & GCC","company":"PassBeyond","location":"Athens","remote":true,"salary":"","posted_at":"","url":"https://sa.linkedin.com/jobs/view/hnw-network-connector-saudi-gcc-at-passbeyond-4405555520?position=21&pageNum=0&refId=lRMZB31aWA2DsqypRP%2FSaw%3D%3D&trackingId=seNv9r7O4CXc0oSDyfPxUA%3D%3D","description":"📍 Remote | Report to Athens HQ 💼 Independent Contractor 💰 Uncapped commission — top performers earn €200,000+\nWho We Are\nWe believe ambitious people should not be prisoners of their passport.PassBeyond helps high-net-worth individuals secure European residency and citizenship through Greek property investment. Our clients invest €250,000–€800,000+ and receive residency or citizenship for themselves and their families — gaining Schengen access, euro-denominated assets, and long-term optionality.\nFounded by Andreas Afeldt, based full-time in Athens, who has spent over a decade working with high-net-worth clients across international markets. PassBeyond sits between global institutional scale and personal, founder-led trust — with deep local knowledge in Greece and cultural fluency across every market we serve.\nThe Role: Bring Your Network. We Bring Everything Else.\nThis is not a traditional sales role, and we are not building a call centre. We are looking exclusively for individuals who have already spent years — sometimes decades — building a personal network of high-net-worth entrepreneurs, business owners, investors, and senior professionals.\nYour network is the asset. Our job is to make it more valuable.\nIf you already move in the right circles, we give you a credible, high-value opportunity to introduce to the people who already trust you — backed by a full operational engine in Athens that handles legal, transactional, and immigration work for you.\nYou will:• Introduce PassBeyond to high-net-worth individuals already in your personal network • Activate dormant relationships with a substantive reason to reconnect • Help clients understand the real numbers, real timelines, and real risks — so they can make an informed decision • Walk alongside clients from first conversation through to permit in hand • Build trust through genuine conversation — not scripts or pressure tactics • Work remotely with full support from our Athens headquarters\nWe are not looking for cold-callers, lead-chasers, or people hoping to build a network from scratch on the job. We are looking for trusted connectors who already have one.\nWho Our Clients Are\n• Entrepreneurs, business owners, and investors with €250,000–€800,000+ to invest • Self-made successes who built wealth through talent and persistence • Often from environments where institutions have failed them — they are sceptical for good reason • Looking for optionality: security, Schengen access, European education, and peace of mind for their families • They value relationships over transactions and will not be rushed or pressured\nOur clients need someone who already understands their world, respects their scepticism, and guides with patience and honesty.\nWhat We're Looking For\nEssential:• An established personal network of high-net-worth individuals you can credibly introduce to a serious opportunity — this is non-negotiable • Cultural fluency — you genuinely belong to the communities you would serve, not just market to them • Fluent English (written and verbal) • Comfortable with commission-only compensation • Integrity — you would rather lose a deal than mislead someone in your network\nHighly Desirable:• Experience in real estate, immigration, wealth management, or financial servicesBackgrounds that often do well:• Business owners and entrepreneurs with peer networks of fellow founders • Private bankers and wealth managers with a client book they can speak to independently • Lawyers and accountants serving affluent clients • Real estate professionals active in investment or luxury markets • Community leaders and well-connected professionals with genuine standing in diaspora or HNW communities\nWhat You Get• Access to training and information about our programmes — no cost to you • Conversation guides designed for high-stakes, trust-based advisory — not generic sales scripts • CRM system for pipeline management • Branded marketing materials ready to share with your contacts • Direct support from our Athens headquarters — legal coordination, transaction management, and immigration filing handled for you • As we grow together, you will receive warm leads from our marketing campaigns alongside your own network"}
