s to signed partnership agreements. The role will also include working cross functionally with Polyphonic Customer Success team on account management and with the Polyphonic global Product and Partnerships teams as we shape the product to reflect what we are hearing from the health systems and how we can best address their needs.\n\nThe person who serves in this role will need to be able to manage complexity, represent J&J to C-Suite stakeholders at hospitals and health tech partners, have commercial/sales skill sets, work with senior stakeholders across J&J, and execute with precision in a cross-functional way. The role requires an understanding of digital solutions in healthcare and experience in commercializing or selling software to healthcare providers as well as experience working in the UAE.\n\nYou Will Be Responsible For\n\nFor the UAE, work with J&J country organizations to maintain up-to-date list of target customers and partners for Polyphonic Surgery and AI Lab based on criteria identified\n\nSegmentation of customers based on established criteriaMaintain airtable/CRM of customer information, including account key stakeholders, mapping of relationships to that account, cloud coverage, J&J history, etc.Keep target account information updated, including adding news, touchpoints by other stakeholders, key innovation initiatives\n\nDrive accounts from prospecting to close, project managing all involved functional and regional stakeholders to get to contract signature\n\nContinuously identify and nurture warm leads to Qualify the account for specific products/modulesBe the voice of the MedTech Digital team in clarifying the value proposition of Polyphonic for customer, leading the customer presentations and demosManage the process of moving customer through sales funnel, ensuring that process is followed and checkpoints achieved for each stage of the sales processProject manage functional involvement (eg Legal, Privacy) and regional involvement (SCM, digital regional team) for each account as it progresses\n\nBuild and manage stakeholder list of key external customers and influencers in region and develop deep relationships\n\nNurture relationships with key decision makers and opinion leaders in the spaceExplore potential partners and liaise with Partnerships lead to surface high potentialsBe the eyes and ears of customer needs and trends in region, feeding back information to G&E and product leaders\n\nRepresent the voice of the UAE customers in cross-functional discussions, helping to shape our customer-facing materials and product roadmap\n\nSupport Marketing lead to develop customer-facing materials and demos, providing a view on what resonatesParticipate in Product-led conversations on roadmap and features that would be most valuable to our customers\n\nBuild and maintain process for sales funnel, both in initial Program as well as Commercial phases\n\nAs we learn through the initial program, continuously document and improve the process by which we move customers through the funnel to contract signatureSet up self-sustaining processes which are needed, eg compliant paymentsSupport setup and updating of CRM/Airtable systemsSupport evolution of Contract frameworks needed as Polyphonic developsAdapt to the changing needs of the role as new product areas arise and will be the leader for UAE commercial activities related to MedTech Digital and Polyphonic.\n\nQualifications / Requirements\n\nRequired Minimum Education: BS in Business, Marketing\n\nRequired Years of Related Experience: 7+ years of relevant experience is required\n\nRequired Knowledge, Skills And Abilities\n\nKnowledge of software in healthcareSales/Business Development experienceUnderstanding of UAE healthcare institutions and stakeholder personas involved in selling software to healthcare providersAbility to work cross sector and influence without authorityOutstanding communication skills; ability to mobilize an organization by setting a vision, providing clarity, and translating strategy into successful executionShown tenacity and energy to inspire change; high tolerance for ambiguity and willingness to adapt to changeDemonstrate strong leadership and interpersonal skills and be able to partner and influence across functions and organizations to drive business goalsTravel approximately 30% mostly within the Middle East or to Santa Clara California, dependent upon business need\n\nRequired Skills\n\nPreferred Skills:\n\nConsulting, Cross-Functional Collaboration, Customer Intelligence, Innovation, Market Expansion, Market Savvy, Medicines and Device Development and Regulation, Relationship Building, Representing, Sales, Sales Presentations, Sales Training, Solutions Selling, Strategic Sales Planning, Sustainable Procurement, Tactical Planning, Technical Credibility, Vendor Selection"}
