ice portfolios\nCarrying out Installation & Commissioning, extension and Maintenance services independently.\nProviding on-site or remote technical support for installation and commissioning of GIS and routine maintenance services, identifying technical problems and making analysis through remote or on-site activity in different Service categories.\nTaking part in pre-commissioning meetings, commissioning planning activities and documentation preparation (e.g. FAT documentation, Site ITPs & ITRs, Method Statements, Control programs, etc.).\nSupporting tendering by providing commissioning plans and time/cost estimation.\nEnsuring compliance with safety regulations and industry standards.\nRecommending customers for immediate and future service requirements, provide feedback to Service Sales team.\nActing as representative of the OEM during interaction with the customer and preparing the tools, equipment and parts needed for a service job and understanding the scope of the job to be performed.\nEnsuring that documentation for the job is available and briefing with service manager, head of department or supervisor about the expected situation on site.\nCreating service reports, time sheets & delivery notes, endorsed by customers.\nEffectively managing multifunctional interfaces - internal, feeder factories, service department, customers, and sub suppliers and abilities to show personal leadership & maintain a teamwork environment to deliver assignments. Strong self-disciplined approach to ensure quality and accuracy of delivery.\nEstablishing long-term customer relationships by understanding customer requirements and applicable regulations, respond immediately to issues and demonstrate in-depth technical service product/solutions knowledge to promote product Life Cycle Management.\nResponsible for adherence to the quality assurance requirements on the Power Plant or Substation or Oil & Gas or process Industries site and seeks to improve these continually.\nYou will be responsible for ensuring compliance with applicable external and internal regulations, procedures, and guidelines.\nLiving Hitachi Energy’s core values safety and integrity, which means taking responsibility for your own actions while caring for your colleagues and the business.\n\nYour background\n\nA bachelor’s degree or Diploma in engineering field is required.\nMinimum 10 years of overall experience, with 6–8 years in High Voltage Equipment installation, testing, commissioning, repair, and maintenance. Proven expertise in Transmission GIS Installation & Commissioning, including substation services and preventive maintenance.\nSolid understanding of switchgear testing and commissioning and other key substation apparatus.\nExperience across the full lifecycle of substation projects—tendering, engineering, and site commissioning. Proficiency in computer applications and strong interpersonal communication skills.\nCertification in Hitachi Energy GIS products is a strong advantage.\nFluency in Arabic is a plus.\nA collaborative team player with a customer-focused mindset and commitment to quality.\nProficiency in both spoken & written English is required.\n\nQualified individuals with a disability may request a reasonable accommodation if you are unable or limited in your ability to use or access the Hitachi Energy career site as a result of your disability. You may request reasonable accommodations by completing a general inquiry form on our website. Please include your contact information and specific details about your required accommodation to support you during the job application process.\n\nThis is solely for job seekers with disabilities requiring accessibility assistance or an accommodation in the job application process. Messages left for other purposes will not receive a response."}
