dards.\n\nIf you are a forward-thinking technologist who believes that AI is the answer to the world's most complex compliance challenges, and you thrive at the intersection of cutting-edge technology and regulatory excellence - you have found your team.\n\nAbout the role\nJoin us as a Staff/Principal Frontend Engineer and play a pivotal role in shaping the future of our cutting-edge applications. Mentor and inspire a top-tier frontend engineering team while staying deeply involved in hands-on coding, about 80% of your time. If you’re passionate about building exceptional user experiences and driving innovation, this is the perfect opportunity for you!\nResponsibilities:\nSpearhead the implementation of new technologies to solve problems and improve existing systems, encourage standardization of best practices & methodologies\nFine-tune the technical stack with a focus on performance, security, stability, and scalability\nWrite client-side code to create super-fast, easy-to-use, web-based applications which include websites for both desktop and mobile browsers, and hybrid in-app pages\nParticipate in design discussions and roadmap planning\nReview and support frontend technical designs across teams to maximize speed and scale\nBuild libraries and frameworks that support complex web applications, speedup development efficiency, and improve code quality\nCoach, mentor, and grow team members\nRequirements:\nBachelor’s/Master’s degree in computer science, engineering, or equivalent industry experience\nMinimum 10+ years of experience in frontend development with 1+ years of experience in a technical leadership role\nHands-on development experience with TypeScript, React and Javascript\nExperience with web services, microservices, APIs, and SOA\nProven track record of delivering projects with high-quality UI\nUnderstanding of state-management patterns such as Redux, Flux, or similar\nAbility to provide technical expertise and complete peer code reviews to team members in