hitecture, capabilities, and best practices\nSupport the design and build of real-world AI use cases, including:\nAI SDR (Sales Development Representative) agents\nCustomer Service / Support agents\nOnboarding and operations agents\nGuide teams on prompt design, orchestration, and agent workflows\nProvide advisory on scaling AI solutions across enterprise environments\nReview and improve existing implementations and use cases\nHelp define internal frameworks, accelerators, and best practices\n\nRequired Experience\nProven experience working with Agentforce (Salesforce AI Agents)\nDemonstrated experience building multiple AI agents end-to-end\nStrong background as a Salesforce Consultant / Architect\nHands-on delivery of AI use cases such as:\nSales automation / SDR agents\nCustomer service automation\nWorkflow automation using AI\nDeep understanding of:\nSalesforce platform (Sales Cloud, Service Cloud, Experience Cloud)\nAI-driven workflows and automation\nPrompt engineering and agent orchestration\nAbility to train, mentor, and communicate complex concepts clearly\n\nWhat We’re Looking For\nSomeone who is genuinely AI-first in their thinking\nA practitioner — not just theory, but real-world delivery experience\nStrong communicator who can lead workshops and influence senior teams\nPassion for building scalable, intelligent solutions\nAbility to work in a fast-moving, high-growth environment\n\nWhy This Role\nWork with a global AI and Salesforce innovation team\nBe part of building next-generation AI products and services\nInfluence how AI is delivered across multiple industries and markets\nLong-term opportunity with consistent engagement and impact\nDirect involvement in cutting-edge Agentforce implementations\n\nEngagement Model\nOngoing contract / advisory role/Perm\nMonthly workshop delivery (core requirement)\nAdditional involvement in solution design and strategic initiatives"}
