earning models.\nProficiency in Python for scripting and automation.\nHands-on experience with Cloud platforms, particularly Azure and GCP.\nPrior experience in addressing scalability and pricing concerns in ML operations.\n\nHow to Apply:\n\nIf you are a passionate ML/Ops professional ready to take on a leadership role or contribute your expertise to a cutting-edge project, we want to hear from you. Please submit your resume, highlighting your relevant experience, and a cover letter detailing your approach to scalability and pricing in ML operations.\n\nNote: This is a unique opportunity to make a significant impact on a client's ML capabilities, and we are excited to welcome individuals who share our enthusiasm for innovation and excellence."}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=f8691e2de62b1006","title":"Salesforce Sales Lead - UAE","company":"Horizontal","location":"{\"city\":\"Dubai\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Dubai\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Dubai\",\"latitude\":25.20485,\"longitude\":55.270782,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"16 hours ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=f8691e2de62b1006","description":"Salesforce Services Sales Lead\n\nAt Horizontal Digital, we hold ourselves to one key belief: You’re only as good as your worst customer experience. This mantra is what drives our digital consultancy to think beyond the easy answers and instead create websites, apps, portals and other experiences that solve customer needs for Fortune 500 companies in intuitive and empathetic ways. And we make this lofty standard a reality by fusing strategy, data, design and technology together to arrive at solutions that set the bar higher for everyone.\n\nWe use these values to fuel superior results:\n\nLock arms\n\nWe forge relationships that make our impact 1,000x stronger. This means working across departments and engaging both our clients and our communities to deliver the greatest good.\n\nShow hustle\n\nWe’re not ones to sit on our hands and wait. Instead, we anticipate opportunities, collectively roll up our sleeves and find ways to execute the exceptional.\n\nEmbrace change\n\nFrom new technologies to workplace philosophies, we welcome the unexpected and constantly anticipate what’s next.\n\nElevate empathy\n\nWe listen before we take action. This means understanding a variety of perspectives and holding ourselves to a higher standard of accountability.\n\nNever settle\n\nWe motivate each other to push past the easy answers and collectively arrive at bigger, more inspiring ideas.\n\nBut enough about us. Let’s talk about you.\n\nWe are seeking a dynamic and results-driven Salesforce Services Sales Lead to drive the growth of our Salesforce professional services business in the Dubai (UAE) region. The ideal candidate will have deep knowledge of the Digital Experience Management and Content Management Platforms (DXP), a strong network within the UAE regions, and a proven track record in enterprise B2B sales. This is a client-facing, quota-carrying role focused on identifying, developing, and closing Salesforce-related service opportunities. Hiring the right person to oversee Salesforce services sales in the UAE requires someone who combines technical understanding, cultural alignment, and proven sales ability and negotiation skills.\n\nIn the DXP world the software sale is typically handled by the vendor itself. Although the software vendor (Salesforce) often consults with an implementation partner like us on product demos, Proof of Concepts, RFP responses and implementation roadmaps, costs and timeline estimates. We are the defacto trusted advisors to the client and Salesforce in ensuring the right products are being purchased by the client to drive their business outcomes.\n\nServices Sales in DXP Platforms such as Salesforce involves:\n\nSelling the design, architecture, and implementation of the digital experience.\nInvolves current state discovery and architecture assessments, future state architecture design, user experience design, integration with various backend systems, CMS platform and components setup, technical development, testing and devops, etc.\nRequires a consultative approach to understand the customer journey and digital strategy and how a DXP Platform fits in to help drive the business outcomes for the customer.\nStrong dependency on our internal strategy, design, engineering, and delivery teams.\nDeep consultative skills, relationship-building ability and outcome-driven. You act like the client’s trusted advisor.\nYour primary buyers are Business Stakeholders, Digital, CRM, CX, Transformation leads and sometimes the IT leaders – so you need to be able to speak their language\nProcurement is often a big part of the close and you need to adept at negotiating with procurement and justifying our value and prowess and sell through at reasonable target margins.\nValue lies in the expertise and ability to deliver results, not the product itself.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n\nDrive end-to-end sales cycles for Salesforce services (implementation, consulting, integration, managed services).\nIdentify and qualify new opportunities across sectors ( travel and tourism, hospitality, real-estate, public sector, telco, banking, retail, etc.).\nBring a network of connections to the table to drive net new Salesforce deals in the region.\nBuild and maintain strong relationships with key decision-makers and stakeholders in target accounts.\nWork closely with our strategy, delivery and technical teams to craft winning proposals and solutions.\nCollaborate with Salesforce account executives and alliances to develop joint go-to-market strategies and execute them with our marketing teams for the region, support them in their deal cycles where they need partner support to close a deal.\nOwn the sales forecast, pipeline development, and deal closure targets in the UAE market.\nStay up to date on the latest and greatest innovations and progress across Salesforce as well as its competitors in the market and have a strong POV on why Salesforce.\n\nRequirements:\n\n5+ years of experience in enterprise software, DXP platforms or consulting services sales, with at least 2+ years in DXP-related offerings.\nStrong understanding of Salesforce products and their business value and how their competitors position.\nDeep knowledge of the UAE market with an existing network in enterprise and/or government sectors.\nDeep understanding of the UAE business culture and decision making process\nArabic fluency is preferred (preferably native or near-native); English proficiency is required.\nExperience working with or within DXP partners\nAbility to work independently, manage complex sales cycles, and build C-level relationships.\nStrong deal closing skills and ability to lead strategic sales pursuits.\nBackground in consulting or advisory roles within the digital transformation space.\n\n Personality & Soft Skills\n\n· Consultative seller — someone who can understand customer pain points and build solutions around Salesforce.\n\n· Excellent communication and presentation skills.\n\n· Highly self-driven, able to work independently or as part of a virtual/global team.\n\nWhat We Offer:\n\nCompetitive base salary + commission structure.\nOpportunity to work with a high-performing regional and global team.\nExposure to cutting-edge Salesforce DXP implementations and innovation in the UAE market.\nCareer growth within a fast-scaling digital transformation leader.\n\nOur UAE Benefits include:\n\n22 working days holiday\nComprehensive medical insurance plan for employee and spouse and children\nVisa for employee and spouse and children\nAnnual return flight to home country for self\nFlexible office times and working from home twice per week\nRemote working from a place of your choice for 2 weeks a year\nFree snacks and drinks in the office\n\nThe above description is not designed to cover or contain a comprehensive listing of activities, duties or responsibilities that are required of the employee for this job. Duties, responsibilities, and activities may change at any time with or without notice."}
